-- European Stocks Advance, Led by Royal Bank, Old Mutual on Return to Profit
-- David Merritt
-- 2010-08-06T07:05:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/european-stocks-advance-led-by-royal-bank-old-mutual-on-return-to-profit.html

          
          
             European stocks advanced, extending a
weekly gain for the Stoxx Europe 600 Index, as Royal Bank of
Scotland Group Plc and Old Mutual Plc returned to profit. Asian
stocks rose and U.S. futures gained.  
 The benchmark Stoxx 600 gained 0.3 percent to 262.43 at
8:03 a.m. in London, heading for a weekly rally of 2.7 percent.
RBS rose 1.9 percent to 53 pence, while Old Mutual surged 4
percent to 128.5 pence.  
 The MSCI Asia Pacific Index climbed 0.3 percent, while
futures on the Standard & Poorâ€™s 500 Index expiring in September
rose 0.1 percent.  
          
          


  


        